%N A306996 Number of primes q < prime(n), such that 4*prime(n) + q is prime.
%C A306996 Conjecture: a(n) > 0 for all n >= 3. - _Dmitry Kamenetsky_, Mar 18 2019
%H A306996 Ashaz Jameel, <a href="/A306996/b306996.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%o A306996 (PARI) a(n) = my(s=0, p=prime(n)); forprime(q=1, p-1, s += isprime(4*p+q)); s; \\ _Michel Marcus_, Mar 26 2026
